## Orchestrator Approval — Phase 4

**Orchestrator:** this session
**Date:** 2026-04-30

### Decision
APPROVED for merge to main, pending human go-ahead.

### Rationale
- Codex GPT-5.5 round 1: REQUEST-CHANGES — two real parser-format defects (comment handling per the decision doc's documented format; quoted scalar inconsistency)
- Codex GPT-5.5 round 2: APPROVED — both fixes correct, no new issues, edge cases verified
- Independent Opus QA (FI-7 separate identity): ALL-PASS on 16 acceptance criteria + 2 spot-checks, with live fixture verification (not just trusting tests)
- Bounded iteration model paid off again: round-1's parser would have rejected the parser's own documented format. The decision-doc regression test now pins parser-vs-decision-doc consistency.

### Iteration record
- Round 1 (5 commits, +51 tests): REQUEST-CHANGES — comment handling, quoted scalar inconsistency
- Round 2 (2 commits, +15 tests): APPROVED — both fixes plus decision-doc regression test plus validate.ts compat fixtures
- Total: 7 commits, +66 tests (187 → 253), run.ts 666 → 773 (+107), package.json unchanged

### What lands
- New artifact type: spec at specs/<id>.md with YAML-style frontmatter (id, title, depends_on)
- Pure parser at tools/pipeline/spec_parse.ts (handles comments, quoted scalars, mixed bare/quoted lists)
- I/O wrapper at tools/specs.ts (loadSpec, ensureIntentForSpec — idempotent intent generation)
- Schema additions: schemas/spec.schema.json new, schemas/intent.schema.json gains optional depends_on
- run.ts spec-first arg disambiguation with legacy intent fallback (backward compat preserved)
- validate.ts integration: spec frontmatter validation, cyclic dependency detection, filename/id mismatch detection, no-specs-mode compatibility
- Phase 5 warning when a spec has depends_on (single-spec case)

### What's deliberately deferred
- Multi-spec arg parsing and dependency-aware execution (Phase 5)
- Memory write-side (deferred per memory_scope_split.md)
- Phases 5-8

### Practical implication for the architecture
After Phase 4, factory has a clean human-authoring surface (specs as markdown with frontmatter). The intent JSON schema becomes derived state — generated from specs at run time. Existing intent-only flows continue to work, so this is fully additive for host projects that haven't adopted the spec convention yet.
